org.shared.array

Class ProtoArray<T extends ProtoArray<T,V,E>,V,E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.shared.array.ProtoArray<T,V,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the parameterization lower bounded by ProtoArray itself.
    V - the storage array type.
    E - the element type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, Array<T,E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractArray, IntegerArray, ObjectArray

    public abstract class ProtoArray<T extends ProtoArray<T,V,E>,V,E>
extends Object
implements Array<T,E>
    An abstract, primordial base class for all multidimensional arrays. Supports operations like mapping, slicing, tiling, shifting, transposition of dimensions, and storage order reversals.

        public T map(T dst,
    int... bounds)
        Description copied from interface: Array
        Maps this array into a destination array.
        Specified by:
        map in interface Array<T extends ProtoArray<T,V,E>,E>
        Parameters:
        dst - the destination array.
        bounds - the mapping bounds as an array of three-tuples. Given the ith tuple, the first component denotes the source start, the second component denotes the destination start, and the third component denotes the mapping size. Is very much the multidimensional analogy to System.arraycopy(Object, int, Object, int, int).
        Returns:
        the destination array.

Given the ith tuple, the first component denotes the source index, the second component denotes the destination index, and the third component denotes the dimension of interest.
